From: ETK GTK Edition <mercurious>
Subject: [PATCH v0.7.2] KERS stage 1 — SEMA PARK: escalate the NV406E semaphore
 WFE spin to a timed futex park (+ sq/sw/pk counters in the perfstat line)

Evidence (2026-07-12, SM8250 pack racing, three 30 s perf samples): the
nv406e::semaphore_acquire wait loop is the hottest single symbol in the
process at 10.7-11.8% of ALL cycles. The ARM64 spin primitive
(spin_on_cacheline_once) is ldaxr+wfe and cannot honor its 100 us bound —
wakes ride the kernel's ~107 us arch-timer event stream AND cacheline
invalidations, and GCM labels are 16 bytes apart (FOUR guest labels per
64 B monitored line; the flip label shares its line with labels 0/2/3), so
neighbor-label traffic turns the wait into a hot spin of spurious wakes.

Change: once a wait has burned GTK_SEMA_SPIN_US (default 150) without the
semaphore changing, each further iteration takes a timed futex park of
GTK_SEMA_PARK_US (default 200) via thread_ctrl::wait_on — a real kernel
sleep — instead of another WFE lap. Releases are plain vm::write with no
futex notify, so the park is timeout-bounded by construction; worst case
adds one park period to an acquire already >150 us old (<=0.6% of a 33 ms
frame). The FLIP semaphore (label_addr+0x10) is excluded: it is the
wedge-prone path the anti-lock nets watch and keeps stock behavior. The
full loop preamble (stop/pause/timeout + on_semaphore_acquire_wait — queued
flips, flush requests) re-runs after every park.

Default ON (house law: new-build features ship on); GTK_SEMA_PARK=0 is the
A/B kill-switch restoring stock spin. Instrumentation is unconditional:
cumulative counters (acquire-waits / wake-iterations / parks) are exported
to the perfstat SHM line as per-interval deltas sq=/sw=/pk= — sw collapsing
toward pk means the spin is parking; large sw with pk=0 means the
kill-switch is active or the spin budget is never reached.

Also bumps the self-ID to "GTK Edition v0.7.2".

Base: v0.0.41-19544-60c9705a + 0.7.0 patch set + perfstat-v1.
Design: ETK dossier KersConcept_20260712.md (S1/K1); validation program
therein (dyno arms, N>=3 warm cells, lock%/wedge-rate regression = kill).

